        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:76:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/75/5412",
        "text": [
          " قَالَ أَبُو جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"اَلْوَصِيَّةُ حَقٌّ وَ قَدْ أَوْصَى رَسُولُ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ فَيَنْبَغِي لِلْمُسْلِمِ أَنْ يُوصِيَ \"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5412 - Al-Ala' narrated from Muhammad ibn Muslim, who said that Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) said:\n\"Making a will is a duty, and the Messenger of Allah (swt) (peace be upon him and his family) indeed made a will. Therefore, it is appropriate for a Muslim to make a will.\""
          ]
        }
      }
